#. <section class="sutta" id="dn4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn4:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Long Discourses 4"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn4:0.2"
msgid "Soṇadaṇḍasutta"
msgstr "With Soṇadaṇḍa"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:0.3"
msgid "1. Campeyyakabrāhmaṇagahapatikā"
msgstr "1. The Brahmins and Householders of Campā"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.111"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "dn4:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "dn4:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅgesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ "
"pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi yena campā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Aṅgas together with "
"a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants when he arrived at Campā,"

msgctxt "dn4:1.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre."
msgstr "where he stayed by the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond."

msgctxt "dn4:1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo campaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ "
"satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena "
"dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the brahmin Soṇadaṇḍa was living in Campā. It was a crown "
"property given by King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha, teeming with living "
"creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the "
"highest quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.112"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:2.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho campeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:"
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Campā heard:"

msgctxt "dn4:2.2"
msgid ""
"“samaṇo khalu bho gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito aṅgesu cārikaṃ "
"caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi campaṃ "
"anuppatto campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre."
msgstr ""
"“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has "
"arrived at Campā and is staying on the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond."

msgctxt "dn4:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

msgctxt "dn4:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "dn4:2.5"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ "
"sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti."
msgstr ""
"He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and "
"Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and "
"he makes it known to others."

msgctxt "dn4:2.6"
msgid ""
"So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ "
"sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

msgctxt "dn4:2.7"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.”"

#. VAR: saṅghasaṅghī → saṅghāsaṅghī (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn4:2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho campeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā campāya nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī "
"gaṇībhūtā yena gaggarā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkamanti."
msgstr ""
"Then, having departed Campā, they formed into companies and headed to the "
"Gaggarā Lotus Pond."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.113"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo uparipāsāde divāseyyaṃ upagato "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the brahmin Soṇadaṇḍa had retired to the upper floor of his "
"stilt longhouse for his midday nap."

#. VAR: saṅghasaṅghī → saṅghāsaṅghī (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn4:3.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo campeyyake brāhmaṇagahapatike campāya "
"nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūte yena gaggarā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkamante."
msgstr "He saw the brahmins and householders heading for the lotus pond,"

msgctxt "dn4:3.3"
msgid "Disvā khattaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed his steward:"

msgctxt "dn4:3.4"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho, bho khatte, campeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā campāya nikkhamitvā "
"saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā yena gaggarā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkamantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“My steward, why are the brahmins and householders headed for the Gaggarā "
"Lotus Pond?”"

msgctxt "dn4:3.5"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, bho, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito aṅgesu cārikaṃ "
"caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi campaṃ "
"anuppatto campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre."
msgstr ""
"“The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Campā and is staying on the banks of the "
"Gaggarā Lotus Pond."

msgctxt "dn4:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

msgctxt "dn4:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "dn4:3.8"
msgid "Tamete bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamantī”ti."
msgstr "They’re going to see that Master Gotama.”"

msgctxt "dn4:3.9"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, bho khatte, yena campeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkama, "
"upasaṅkamitvā campeyyake brāhmaṇagahapatike evaṃ vadehi:"
msgstr "“Well then, go to the brahmins and householders and say to them:"

msgctxt "dn4:3.10"
msgid "‘soṇadaṇḍo, bho, brāhmaṇo evamāha—"
msgstr "‘Sirs, the brahmin Soṇadaṇḍa asks"

msgctxt "dn4:3.11"
msgid ""
"āgamentu kira bhavanto, soṇadaṇḍopi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamissatī’”ti."
msgstr "you to wait, as he will also go to see the ascetic Gotama.’”"

msgctxt "dn4:3.12"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so khattā soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena "
"campeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā campeyyake "
"brāhmaṇagahapatike etadavoca:"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied the steward, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn4:3.13"
msgid "“soṇadaṇḍo bho brāhmaṇo evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:3.14"
msgid ""
"‘āgamentu kira bhavanto, soṇadaṇḍopi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:3.15"
msgid "2. Soṇadaṇḍaguṇakathā"
msgstr "2. The Qualities of Soṇadaṇḍa"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena nānāverajjakānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pañcamattāni "
"brāhmaṇasatāni campāyaṃ paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time around five hundred brahmins from abroad were residing in "
"Campā on some business."

msgctxt "dn4:4.2"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho te brāhmaṇā:"
msgstr "They heard that"

msgctxt "dn4:4.3"
msgid "“soṇadaṇḍo kira brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti."
msgstr "the brahmin Soṇadaṇḍa was going to see the ascetic Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te brāhmaṇā yena soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "They approached Soṇadaṇḍa and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn4:4.5"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it really true that you are going to see the ascetic Gotama?”"

msgctxt "dn4:4.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ kho me, bho, hoti:"
msgstr "“Yes, gentlemen, it is true.”"

msgctxt "dn4:4.7"
msgid "‘ahampi samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.1"
msgid "“Mā bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkami."
msgstr "“Please don’t, master Soṇadaṇḍa!"

# Text omits expected samaṇotveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ caṅkiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. see MN 95, which includes this.
msgctxt "dn4:5.2"
msgid "Na arahati bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "It’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:5.3"
msgid ""
"Sace bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissati, bhoto "
"soṇadaṇḍassa yaso hāyissati, samaṇassa gotamassa yaso abhivaḍḍhissati."
msgstr "For if you do so, your reputation will diminish and his will increase."

msgctxt "dn4:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yampi bhoto soṇadaṇḍassa yaso hāyissati, samaṇassa gotamassa yaso "
"abhivaḍḍhissati, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ "
"dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama;"

msgctxt "dn4:5.5"
msgid ""
"samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ soṇadaṇḍaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.6"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva "
"sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena."
msgstr ""
"You are well born on both your mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, "
"irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh "
"paternal generation."

msgctxt "dn4:5.7"
msgid ""
"Yampi bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko "
"yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na "
"arahati bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama;"

msgctxt "dn4:5.8"
msgid ""
"samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ soṇadaṇḍaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.9"
msgid "Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo … pe …"
msgstr "You’re rich, affluent, and wealthy. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.114"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.10"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo ajjhāyako mantadharo tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū "
"sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako "
"veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You recite and remember the hymns, and are an expert in the three Vedas, "
"together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the "
"testament as fifth. You know philology and grammar, and are well versed in "
"cosmology and the marks of a great man. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: brahmavacchasī → brahmavaccasī (bj, pts1) | brahmavacchasi (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn4:5.11"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya "
"samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You are attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. You are "
"magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.12"
msgid "Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo sīlavā vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato … pe …"
msgstr "You are ethical, mature in ethical conduct. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: anelagalāya → aneḷagalāya (pts1) | anelagaḷāya (mr)
msgctxt "dn4:5.13"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato "
"vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that "
"expresses the meaning. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.14"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo tīṇi māṇavakasatāni mante vāceti. "
"Bahū kho pana nānādisā nānājanapadā māṇavakā āgacchanti bhoto soṇadaṇḍassa "
"santike mantatthikā mante adhiyitukāmā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You teach the teachers of many, and teach three hundred students to recite "
"the hymns. Many students come from various districts and countries for the "
"sake of the hymns, wishing to learn the hymns. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.15"
msgid "Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto;"
msgstr ""
"You’re old, elderly and senior, advanced in years, and have reached the "
"final stage of life."

msgctxt "dn4:5.16"
msgid "samaṇo gotamo taruṇo ceva taruṇapabbajito ca … pe …"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama is young, and has newly gone forth. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.17"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa sakkato garukato "
"mānito pūjito apacito … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You’re honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by King "
"Bimbisāra of Magadha …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.18"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa sakkato garukato mānito "
"pūjito apacito … pe …"
msgstr "and the brahmin Pokkharasāti. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:5.19"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi soṇadaṇḍo campaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ "
"sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ, raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena dinnaṃ, "
"rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"You live in Campā, a crown property given by King Seniya Bimbisāra of "
"Magadha, teeming with living creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, "
"a royal endowment of the highest quality."

msgctxt "dn4:5.20"
msgid ""
"Yampi bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo campaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ "
"sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ, raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena dinnaṃ, "
"rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:5.21"
msgid ""
"Imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For this reason, too, it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic "
"Gotama;"

msgctxt "dn4:5.22"
msgid ""
"samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ soṇadaṇḍaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitun”ti."
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:5.23"
msgid "3. Buddhaguṇakathā"
msgstr "3. The Qualities of the Buddha"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr "When they had spoken, Soṇadaṇḍa said to those brahmins:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.115"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.2"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, bho, mamapi suṇātha, yathā mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ "
"dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, gentlemen, listen to why it’s appropriate for me to go to see "
"the ascetic Gotama,"

msgctxt "dn4:6.3"
msgid "na tveva arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "and it’s not appropriate for him to come to see me."

msgctxt "dn4:6.4"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā, akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho "
"jātivādena."
msgstr ""
"He is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, "
"irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh "
"paternal generation."

msgctxt "dn4:6.5"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bho, samaṇo gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā, akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho "
"jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For this reason it’s not appropriate for the ascetic Gotama to come to see "
"me;"

msgctxt "dn4:6.6"
msgid ""
"atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.7"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo mahantaṃ ñātisaṅghaṃ ohāya pabbajito … pe …"
msgstr "When he went forth he abandoned a large family circle. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.8"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ ohāya pabbajito "
"bhūmigatañca vehāsaṭṭhaṃ ca … pe …"
msgstr ""
"When he went forth he abandoned abundant gold coin and bullion stored in "
"dungeons and towers. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.9"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo daharova samāno yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena "
"yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He went forth from the lay life to homelessness while still a youth, young, "
"black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.10"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ "
"kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajito … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Though his mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces, "
"he shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth "
"from the lay life to homelessness. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.11"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya "
"vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, brahmavaṇṇī, brahmavacchasī, akhuddāvakāso "
"dassanāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He is "
"magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.12"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sīlavā ariyasīlī kusalasīlī kusalasīlena "
"samannāgato … pe …"
msgstr "He is ethical, possessing ethical conduct that is noble and skillful. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.13"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya "
"samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He’s a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that "
"expresses the meaning. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.14"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo … pe …"
msgstr "He’s a teacher of teachers. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.15"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo khīṇakāmarāgo vigatacāpallo … pe …"
msgstr "He has ended sensual desire, and is rid of caprice. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.16"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kammavādī kiriyavādī apāpapurekkhāro brahmaññāya "
"pajāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He teaches the efficacy of deeds and action. He doesn’t wish any harm upon "
"the community of brahmins. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.17"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo uccā kulā pabbajito asambhinnakhattiyakulā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He went forth from an eminent family of unbroken aristocratic lineage. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.18"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo aḍḍhā kulā pabbajito mahaddhanā mahābhogā … pe …"
msgstr "He went forth from a rich, affluent, and wealthy family. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.116"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.19"
msgid ""
"Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ tiroraṭṭhā tirojanapadā pañhaṃ pucchituṃ "
"āgacchanti … pe …"
msgstr "People come from distant lands and distant countries to question him. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.20"
msgid ""
"Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ anekāni devatāsahassāni pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gatāni … "
"pe …"
msgstr "Many thousands of deities have gone for refuge for life to him. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.21"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

msgctxt "dn4:6.22"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.23"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato … pe …"
msgstr "He has the thirty-two marks of a great man. …"

# This description also at Ss 13
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.24"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo ehisvāgatavādī sakhilo sammodako abbhākuṭiko "
"uttānamukho pubbabhāsī … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He is welcoming, congenial, polite, smiling, open, the first to speak. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.25"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo catunnaṃ parisānaṃ sakkato garukato mānito pūjito "
"apacito … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He’s honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by the four "
"assemblies. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.26"
msgid "Samaṇe khalu, bho, gotame bahū devā ca manussā ca abhippasannā … pe …"
msgstr "Many gods and humans are devoted to him. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.27"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo yasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā paṭivasati, na tasmiṃ "
"gāme vā nigame vā amanussā manusse viheṭhenti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"While he is residing in a village or town, non-human entities do not harass "
"them. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.28"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo saṅghī gaṇī gaṇācariyo puthutitthakarānaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati. Yathā kho pana, bho, etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ yathā vā tathā "
"vā yaso samudāgacchati, na hevaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa yaso samudāgato."
msgstr ""
"He leads an order and a community, and teaches a community, and is said to "
"be the best of the various religious founders. He didn’t come by his fame in "
"the same ways as those other ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "dn4:6.29"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya samaṇassa gotamassa yaso samudāgato "
"… pe …"
msgstr "Rather, he came by his fame due to his supreme knowledge and conduct. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.30"
msgid ""
"Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro saputto sabhariyo "
"sapariso sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …"
msgstr ""
"King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha and his wives and children have gone for "
"refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.31"
msgid ""
"Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo saputto sabhariyo sapariso "
"sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …"
msgstr ""
"King Pasenadi of Kosala and his wives and children have gone for refuge for "
"life to the ascetic Gotama. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.32"
msgid ""
"Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti saputto sabhariyo sapariso "
"sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …"
msgstr ""
"The brahmin Pokkharasāti and his wives and children have gone for refuge for "
"life to the ascetic Gotama. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.33"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa sakkato "
"garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He’s honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by King Bimbisāra "
"of Magadha …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.34"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sakkato garukato "
"mānito pūjito apacito … pe …"
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.35"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa sakkato garukato "
"mānito pūjito apacito … pe …"
msgstr "and the brahmin Pokkharasāti."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.117"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:6.36"
msgid ""
"Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo campaṃ anuppatto, campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya "
"pokkharaṇiyā tīre."
msgstr ""
"The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Campā and is staying at the Gaggarā Lotus "
"Pond."

msgctxt "dn4:6.37"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, bho, keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā amhākaṃ gāmakhettaṃ āgacchanti "
"atithī no te honti."
msgstr ""
"Any ascetic or brahmin who comes to stay in our village district is our "
"guest,"

msgctxt "dn4:6.38"
msgid ""
"Atithī kho panamhehi sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā apacetabbā."
msgstr "and should be honored and respected as such."

msgctxt "dn4:6.39"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bho, samaṇo gotamo campaṃ anuppatto campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya "
"pokkharaṇiyā tīre, atithimhākaṃ samaṇo gotamo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:6.40"
msgid ""
"atithi kho panamhehi sakkātabbo garukātabbo mānetabbo pūjetabbo apacetabbo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:6.41"
msgid ""
"Imināpaṅgena na arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr ""
"For this reason, too, it’s not appropriate for Master Gotama to come to see "
"me;"

msgctxt "dn4:6.42"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him."

msgctxt "dn4:6.43"
msgid ""
"Ettake kho ahaṃ, bho, tassa bhoto gotamassa vaṇṇe pariyāpuṇāmi, no ca kho so "
"bhavaṃ gotamo ettakavaṇṇo."
msgstr ""
"This is the extent of Master Gotama’s praise that I have learned. But his "
"praises are not confined to this,"

msgctxt "dn4:6.44"
msgid "Aparimāṇavaṇṇo hi so bhavaṃ gotamo”ti."
msgstr "for the praise of Master Gotama is limitless.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te brāhmaṇā soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, those brahmins said to him:"

msgctxt "dn4:7.2"
msgid ""
"“yathā kho bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇassa gotamassa vaṇṇe bhāsati ito cepi so "
"bhavaṃ gotamo yojanasate viharati, alameva saddhena kulaputtena dassanāya "
"upasaṅkamituṃ api puṭosenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“According to Soṇadaṇḍa’s praises, if Master Gotama were staying within a "
"hundred leagues, it’d be worthwhile for a faithful person of good family to "
"go to see him, even if they had to carry their own provisions in a shoulder "
"bag.”"

msgctxt "dn4:7.3"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, bho, sabbeva mayaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, gentlemen, let’s all go to see the ascetic Gotama.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:7.4"
msgid "4. Soṇadaṇḍaparivitakka"
msgstr "4. Soṇadaṇḍa’s Second Thoughts"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.118"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:7.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ yena gaggarā "
"pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then Soṇadaṇḍa together with a large group of brahmins went to see the "
"Buddha."

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs8"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa tirovanasaṇḍagatassa evaṃ cetaso "
"parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"But as he reached the far side of the forest, this thought came to mind:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.2"
msgid "“ahañceva kho pana samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyaṃ;"
msgstr "“Suppose I was to ask the ascetic Gotama a question."

msgctxt "dn4:8.3"
msgid "tatra ce maṃ samaṇo gotamo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "He might say to me:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.4"
msgid ""
"‘na kho esa, brāhmaṇa, pañho evaṃ pucchitabbo, evaṃ nāmesa, brāhmaṇa, pañho "
"pucchitabbo’ti, tena maṃ ayaṃ parisā paribhaveyya:"
msgstr ""
"‘Brahmin, you shouldn’t ask your question like that. This is how you should "
"ask it.’ And the assembly might disparage me for that:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.5"
msgid ""
"‘bālo soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abyatto, nāsakkhi samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ yoniso pañhaṃ "
"pucchitun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Soṇadaṇḍa is foolish and incompetent. He’s not able to properly ask the "
"ascetic Gotama a question.’"

msgctxt "dn4:8.6"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāyaṃ parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr "And when you’re disparaged by the assembly, your reputation diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.7"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr "When your reputation diminishes, your wealth also diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.8"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr "But my wealth relies on my reputation."

msgctxt "dn4:8.9"
msgid ""
"Mamañceva kho pana samaṇo gotamo pañhaṃ puccheyya, tassa cāhaṃ pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ na ārādheyyaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Or if the ascetic Gotama asks me a question, I might not satisfy him with my "
"answer."

msgctxt "dn4:8.10"
msgid "tatra ce maṃ samaṇo gotamo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "He might say to me:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.11"
msgid ""
"‘na kho esa, brāhmaṇa, pañho evaṃ byākātabbo, evaṃ nāmesa, brāhmaṇa, pañho "
"byākātabbo’ti, tena maṃ ayaṃ parisā paribhaveyya:"
msgstr ""
"‘Brahmin, you shouldn’t answer the question like that. This is how you "
"should answer it.’ And the assembly might disparage me for that:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.12"
msgid ""
"‘bālo soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abyatto, nāsakkhi samaṇassa gotamassa pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādhetun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Soṇadaṇḍa is foolish and incompetent. He’s not able to satisfy the ascetic "
"Gotama’s mind with his answer.’"

msgctxt "dn4:8.13"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāyaṃ parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr "And when you’re disparaged by the assembly, your reputation diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.14"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr "When your reputation diminishes, your wealth also diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.15"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr "But my wealth relies on my reputation."

msgctxt "dn4:8.16"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana evaṃ samīpagato samāno adisvāva samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ "
"nivatteyyaṃ, tena maṃ ayaṃ parisā paribhaveyya:"
msgstr ""
"On the other hand, if I were to turn back after having come so far without "
"having seen the ascetic Gotama, the assembly might disparage me for that:"

msgctxt "dn4:8.17"
msgid ""
"‘bālo soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abyatto mānathaddho bhīto ca, no visahati samaṇaṃ "
"gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ, kathañhi nāma evaṃ samīpagato samāno adisvā "
"samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ nivattissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Soṇadaṇḍa is foolish and incompetent. He’s stuck-up and scared. He doesn’t "
"dare to go and see the ascetic Gotama. For how on earth can he turn back "
"after having come so far without having seen the ascetic Gotama!’"

msgctxt "dn4:8.18"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāyaṃ parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr "And when you’re disparaged by the assembly, your reputation diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.19"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "When your reputation diminishes, your wealth also diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:8.20"
msgid "yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā”ti."
msgstr "But my wealth relies on my reputation.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:9.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "Then Soṇadaṇḍa went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn4:9.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side."

msgctxt "dn4:9.3"
msgid ""
"Campeyyakāpi kho brāhmaṇagahapatikā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ "
"kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā "
"tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Before sitting down to one side, some of the brahmins and householders of "
"Campā bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up "
"their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, "
"while some kept silent.     "

# Given the Buddha’s savage takedown of Ambattha, perhaps Sonadanda’s worries were not completely misplaced!
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs10"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.119"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:10.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo etadeva bahulamanuvitakkento nisinno hoti:"
msgstr ""
"But while sitting there, Soṇadaṇḍa continued to be plagued by many second "
"thoughts. He thought:"

msgctxt "dn4:10.2"
msgid "“ahañceva kho pana samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.3"
msgid "tatra ce maṃ samaṇo gotamo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.4"
msgid ""
"‘na kho esa, brāhmaṇa, pañho evaṃ pucchitabbo, evaṃ nāmesa, brāhmaṇa, pañho "
"pucchitabbo’ti, tena maṃ ayaṃ parisā paribhaveyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.5"
msgid ""
"‘bālo soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abyatto, nāsakkhi samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ yoniso pañhaṃ "
"pucchitun’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.6"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāyaṃ parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.7"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.8"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.9"
msgid ""
"Mamañceva kho pana samaṇo gotamo pañhaṃ puccheyya, tassa cāhaṃ pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ na ārādheyyaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.10"
msgid "tatra ce maṃ samaṇo gotamo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.11"
msgid ""
"‘na kho esa, brāhmaṇa, pañho evaṃ byākātabbo, evaṃ nāmesa, brāhmaṇa, pañho "
"byākātabbo’ti, tena maṃ ayaṃ parisā paribhaveyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.12"
msgid ""
"‘bālo soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abyatto, nāsakkhi samaṇassa gotamassa pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādhetun’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.13"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāyaṃ parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.14"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.15"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:10.16"
msgid ""
"Aho vata maṃ samaṇo gotamo sake ācariyake tevijjake pañhaṃ puccheyya, addhā "
"vatassāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādheyyaṃ pañhassa veyyākaraṇenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“If only the ascetic Gotama would ask me about my own teacher’s scriptural "
"heritage of the three Vedas! Then I could definitely satisfy his mind with "
"my answer.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:10.17"
msgid "5. Brāhmaṇapaññatti"
msgstr "5. What Makes a Brahmin"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:11.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavato soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing what Soṇadaṇda was thinking, thought:"

msgctxt "dn4:11.2"
msgid "“vihaññati kho ayaṃ soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo sakena cittena."
msgstr "“This brahmin Soṇadaṇḍa is worried by his own thoughts."

msgctxt "dn4:11.3"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sake ācariyake tevijjake pañhaṃ "
"puccheyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I ask him about his own teacher’s scriptural heritage of the three "
"Vedas?”"

msgctxt "dn4:11.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So he said to Soṇadaṇḍa:"

msgctxt "dn4:11.5"
msgid ""
"“katihi pana, brāhmaṇa, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, how many factors must a brahmin possess for the brahmins to "
"describe him as a brahmin;"

msgctxt "dn4:11.6"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"and so that when he says ‘I am a brahmin’ he speaks rightly, without falling "
"into falsehood?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs12"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.120"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Soṇadaṇḍa thought:"

msgctxt "dn4:12.2"
msgid ""
"“yaṃ vata no ahosi icchitaṃ, yaṃ ākaṅkhitaṃ, yaṃ adhippetaṃ, yaṃ "
"abhipatthitaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“The ascetic Gotama has asked me about exactly what I wanted, what I wished "
"for, what I desired, what I yearned for; that is, my own scriptural heritage."

msgctxt "dn4:12.3"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata maṃ samaṇo gotamo sake ācariyake tevijjake pañhaṃ puccheyya, addhā "
"vatassāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādheyyaṃ pañhassa veyyākaraṇenā’ti, tatra maṃ samaṇo "
"gotamo sake ācariyake tevijjake pañhaṃ pucchati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:12.4"
msgid "Addhā vatassāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādhessāmi pañhassa veyyākaraṇenā”ti."
msgstr "I can definitely satisfy his mind with my answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo abbhunnāmetvā kāyaṃ anuviloketvā parisaṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Soṇadaṇḍa straightened his back, looked around the assembly, and said "
"to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn4:13.2"
msgid ""
"“pañcahi, bho gotama, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, a brahmin must possess five factors for the brahmins to "
"describe him as a brahmin;"

msgctxt "dn4:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"and so that when he says ‘I am a brahmin’ he speaks rightly, without falling "
"into falsehood."

msgctxt "dn4:13.4"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "dn4:13.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a brahmin is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of "
"pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to "
"the seventh paternal generation."

msgctxt "dn4:13.6"
msgid ""
"ajjhāyako hoti mantadharo tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ "
"sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako veyyākaraṇo "
"lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo;"
msgstr ""
"He recites and remembers the hymns, and is an expert in the three Vedas, "
"together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the "
"testament as fifth. He knows philology and grammar, and is well versed in "
"cosmology and the marks of a great man."

msgctxt "dn4:13.7"
msgid ""
"abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato "
"brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya;"
msgstr ""
"He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He is "
"magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold."

msgctxt "dn4:13.8"
msgid "sīlavā hoti vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato;"
msgstr "He is ethical, mature in ethical conduct."

msgctxt "dn4:13.9"
msgid "paṇḍito ca hoti medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He’s astute and clever, being the first or second to hold the sacrificial "
"ladle."

msgctxt "dn4:13.10"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bho gotama, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ "
"paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"These are the five factors which a brahmin must possess for the brahmins to "
"describe him as a brahmin;"

msgctxt "dn4:13.11"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"and so that when he says ‘I am a brahmin’ he speaks rightly, without falling "
"into falsehood.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.121"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc54"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Imesaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, pañcannaṃ aṅgānaṃ sakkā ekaṃ aṅgaṃ ṭhapayitvā "
"catūhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“But brahmin, is it possible to set aside one of these five factors and "
"still rightly describe someone as a brahmin?”"

msgctxt "dn4:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:14.3"
msgid "“Sakkā, bho gotama."
msgstr "“It is possible, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:14.4"
msgid "Imesañhi, bho gotama, pañcannaṃ aṅgānaṃ vaṇṇaṃ ṭhapayāma."
msgstr "We could leave appearance out of the five factors."

msgctxt "dn4:14.5"
msgid "Kiñhi vaṇṇo karissati?"
msgstr "For what does appearance matter?"

msgctxt "dn4:14.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:14.7"
msgid ""
"ajjhāyako ca hoti mantadharo ca tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ "
"sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako veyyākaraṇo "
"lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:14.8"
msgid "sīlavā ca hoti vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:14.9"
msgid "paṇḍito ca hoti medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:14.10"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bho gotama, catūhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ "
"paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"A brahmin must possess the remaining four factors for the brahmins to "
"rightly describe him as a brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn4:14.11"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc55"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Imesaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, catunnaṃ aṅgānaṃ sakkā ekaṃ aṅgaṃ ṭhapayitvā "
"tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“But brahmin, is it possible to set aside one of these four factors and "
"still rightly describe someone as a brahmin?”"

msgctxt "dn4:15.2"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:15.3"
msgid "“Sakkā, bho gotama."
msgstr "“It is possible, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:15.4"
msgid "Imesañhi, bho gotama, catunnaṃ aṅgānaṃ mante ṭhapayāma."
msgstr "We could leave the hymns out of the five factors."

# This doesn’t strike me as particularly plausible.
msgctxt "dn4:15.5"
msgid "Kiñhi mantā karissanti?"
msgstr "For what do the hymns matter?"

msgctxt "dn4:15.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:15.7"
msgid "sīlavā ca hoti vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:15.8"
msgid "paṇḍito ca hoti medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:15.9"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bho gotama, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"A brahmin must possess the remaining three factors for the brahmins to "
"rightly describe him as a brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn4:15.10"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc56"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:16.1"
msgid ""
"“Imesaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, tiṇṇaṃ aṅgānaṃ sakkā ekaṃ aṅgaṃ ṭhapayitvā "
"dvīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“But brahmin, is it possible to set aside one of these three factors and "
"still rightly describe someone as a brahmin?”"

msgctxt "dn4:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:16.3"
msgid "“Sakkā, bho gotama."
msgstr "“It is possible, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:16.4"
msgid "Imesañhi, bho gotama, tiṇṇaṃ aṅgānaṃ jātiṃ ṭhapayāma."
msgstr "We could leave birth out of the five factors."

msgctxt "dn4:16.5"
msgid "Kiñhi jāti karissati?"
msgstr "For what does birth matter?"

msgctxt "dn4:16.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo sīlavā hoti vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena "
"samannāgato;"
msgstr "It’s when a brahmin is ethical, mature in ethical conduct;"

msgctxt "dn4:16.7"
msgid "paṇḍito ca hoti medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"and he’s astute and clever, being the first or second to hold the "
"sacrificial ladle."

msgctxt "dn4:16.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bho gotama, dvīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"A brahmin must possess these two factors for the brahmins to rightly "
"describe him as a brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn4:16.9"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.122"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc57"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te brāhmaṇā soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, those brahmins said to him:"

msgctxt "dn4:17.2"
msgid "“mā bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo evaṃ avaca, mā bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo evaṃ avaca."
msgstr "“Please don’t say that, Master Soṇadaṇda, please don’t say that!"

msgctxt "dn4:17.3"
msgid ""
"Apavadateva bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo vaṇṇaṃ, apavadati mante, apavadati jātiṃ, "
"ekaṃsena bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇasseva gotamassa vādaṃ anupakkhandatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"You’re just condemning appearance, the hymns, and birth! You’re totally "
"going over to the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc58"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:18.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to them:"

msgctxt "dn4:18.2"
msgid "“sace kho tumhākaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“Well, brahmins, if you think that"

msgctxt "dn4:18.3"
msgid ""
"‘appassuto ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, akalyāṇavākkaraṇo ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, "
"duppañño ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, na ca pahoti soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo samaṇena "
"gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun’ti, tiṭṭhatu soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, "
"tumhe mayā saddhiṃ mantavho asmiṃ vacane."
msgstr ""
"Soṇadaṇḍa is uneducated, a poor speaker, witless, and not capable of having "
"a dialogue with me about this, then leave him aside and you can have a "
"dialogue with me."

msgctxt "dn4:18.4"
msgid "Sace pana tumhākaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "But if you think that"

msgctxt "dn4:18.5"
msgid ""
"‘bahussuto ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, kalyāṇavākkaraṇo ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, "
"paṇḍito ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo, pahoti ca soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo samaṇena "
"gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun’ti, tiṭṭhatha tumhe, soṇadaṇḍo "
"brāhmaṇo mayā saddhiṃ paṭimantetū”ti."
msgstr ""
"he’s learned, a good speaker, astute, and capable of having a dialogue with "
"me about this, then you should stand aside and let him have a dialogue with "
"me.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs19"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.123"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc59"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:19.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Soṇadaṇḍa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn4:19.2"
msgid ""
"“tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tuṇhī bhavaṃ gotamo hotu, ahameva tesaṃ "
"sahadhammena paṭivacanaṃ karissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Let it be, Master Gotama, be silent. I myself will respond to them in a "
"legitimate manner.”"

msgctxt "dn4:19.3"
msgid "Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he said to those brahmins:"

msgctxt "dn4:19.4"
msgid "“mā bhavanto evaṃ avacuttha, mā bhavanto evaṃ avacuttha:"
msgstr "“Don’t say this, gentlemen, don’t say this:"

msgctxt "dn4:19.5"
msgid ""
"‘apavadateva bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo vaṇṇaṃ, apavadati mante, apavadati jātiṃ, "
"ekaṃsena bhavaṃ soṇadaṇḍo samaṇasseva gotamassa vādaṃ anupakkhandatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘You’re just condemning appearance, the hymns, and birth! You’re totally "
"going over to the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine!’"

msgctxt "dn4:19.6"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, bho, apavadāmi vaṇṇaṃ vā mante vā jātiṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "I’m not condemning appearance, hymns, or birth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc60"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:20.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa bhāgineyyo aṅgako nāma "
"māṇavako tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Soṇadaṇḍa’s nephew, the student Aṅgaka was sitting in that "
"assembly."

msgctxt "dn4:20.2"
msgid "Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Soṇadaṇḍa said to those brahmins:"

msgctxt "dn4:20.3"
msgid "“passanti no bhonto imaṃ aṅgakaṃ māṇavakaṃ amhākaṃ bhāgineyyan”ti?"
msgstr "“Gentlemen, do you see my nephew, the student Aṅgaka?”"

msgctxt "dn4:20.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn4:20.5"
msgid ""
"“Aṅgako kho, bho, māṇavako abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya "
"vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso "
"dassanāya, nāssa imissaṃ parisāyaṃ samasamo atthi vaṇṇena ṭhapetvā samaṇaṃ "
"gotamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Aṅgaka is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He is "
"magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. There’s no-one in this assembly "
"so good-looking, apart from the ascetic Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:20.6"
msgid ""
"Aṅgako kho māṇavako ajjhāyako mantadharo, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū "
"sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako "
"veyyākaraṇo lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo."
msgstr ""
"Aṅgaka recites and remembers the hymns, and is an expert in the three Vedas, "
"together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the "
"testament as fifth. He knows philology and grammar, and is well versed in "
"cosmology and the marks of a great man."

msgctxt "dn4:20.7"
msgid "Ahamassa mante vācetā."
msgstr "And I am the one who teaches him the hymns."

msgctxt "dn4:20.8"
msgid ""
"Aṅgako kho māṇavako ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva "
"sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena."
msgstr ""
"Aṅgaka is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, "
"irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh "
"paternal generation."

msgctxt "dn4:20.9"
msgid "Ahamassa mātāpitaro jānāmi."
msgstr "And I know his mother and father."

msgctxt "dn4:20.10"
msgid ""
"Aṅgako kho māṇavako pāṇampi haneyya, adinnampi ādiyeyya, paradārampi "
"gaccheyya, musāvādampi bhaṇeyya, majjampi piveyya, ettha dāni, bho, kiṃ "
"vaṇṇo karissati, kiṃ mantā, kiṃ jāti?"
msgstr ""
"But if Aṅgaka were to kill living creatures, steal, commit adultery, lie, "
"and drink alcohol, then what’s the use of his appearance, his hymns, or his "
"birth?"

msgctxt "dn4:20.11"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho, brāhmaṇo sīlavā ca hoti vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato, "
msgstr "It’s when a brahmin is ethical, mature in ethical conduct; "

msgctxt "dn4:20.12"
msgid "paṇḍito ca hoti medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"and he’s astute and clever, being the first or second to hold the "
"sacrificial ladle."

msgctxt "dn4:20.13"
msgid "Imehi kho, bho, dvīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapenti;"
msgstr ""
"A brahmin must possess these two factors for the brahmins to rightly "
"describe him as a brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn4:20.14"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:20.15"
msgid "6. Sīlapaññākathā"
msgstr "6. The Discussion of Ethics and Wisdom"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.124"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc61"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Imesaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, dvinnaṃ aṅgānaṃ sakkā ekaṃ aṅgaṃ ṭhapayitvā ekena "
"aṅgena samannāgataṃ brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ paññapetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“But brahmin, is it possible to set aside one of these two factors and still "
"rightly describe someone as a brahmin?”"

msgctxt "dn4:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘brāhmaṇosmī’ti ca vadamāno sammā vadeyya, na ca pana musāvādaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:21.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:21.4"
msgid "Sīlaparidhotā hi, bho gotama, paññā; paññāparidhotaṃ sīlaṃ."
msgstr "For wisdom is cleansed by ethics, and ethics are cleansed by wisdom."

msgctxt "dn4:21.5"
msgid "Yattha sīlaṃ tattha paññā, yattha paññā tattha sīlaṃ."
msgstr "Ethics and wisdom always go together."

msgctxt "dn4:21.6"
msgid "Sīlavato paññā, paññavato sīlaṃ."
msgstr "An ethical person is wise, and a wise person ethical."

msgctxt "dn4:21.7"
msgid "Sīlapaññāṇañca pana lokasmiṃ aggamakkhāyati."
msgstr "And ethics and wisdom are said to be the best things in the world."

msgctxt "dn4:21.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, hatthena vā hatthaṃ dhoveyya, pādena vā pādaṃ "
"dhoveyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s just like when you clean one hand with the other, or clean one foot "
"with the other."

msgctxt "dn4:21.9"
msgid "evameva kho, bho gotama, sīlaparidhotā paññā, paññāparidhotaṃ sīlaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, wisdom is cleansed by ethics, and ethics are cleansed by "
"wisdom."

msgctxt "dn4:21.10"
msgid "Yattha sīlaṃ tattha paññā, yattha paññā tattha sīlaṃ."
msgstr "Ethics and wisdom always go together."

msgctxt "dn4:21.11"
msgid "Sīlavato paññā, paññavato sīlaṃ."
msgstr "An ethical person is wise, and a wise person ethical."

msgctxt "dn4:21.12"
msgid "Sīlapaññāṇañca pana lokasmiṃ aggamakkhāyatī”ti."
msgstr "And ethics and wisdom are said to be the best things in the world.”"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs22"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sīlaparidhotā hi, brāhmaṇa, paññā, "
"paññāparidhotaṃ sīlaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“That’s so true, brahmin, that’s so true! For wisdom is cleansed by ethics, "
"and ethics are cleansed by wisdom."

msgctxt "dn4:22.2"
msgid "Yattha sīlaṃ tattha paññā, yattha paññā tattha sīlaṃ."
msgstr "Ethics and wisdom always go together."

msgctxt "dn4:22.3"
msgid "Sīlavato paññā, paññavato sīlaṃ."
msgstr "An ethical person is wise, and a wise person ethical."

msgctxt "dn4:22.4"
msgid "Sīlapaññāṇañca pana lokasmiṃ aggamakkhāyati."
msgstr "And ethics and wisdom are said to be the best things in the world."

msgctxt "dn4:22.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, hatthena vā hatthaṃ dhoveyya, pādena vā pādaṃ dhoveyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s just like when you clean one hand with the other, or clean one foot "
"with the other."

msgctxt "dn4:22.6"
msgid "evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, sīlaparidhotā paññā, paññāparidhotaṃ sīlaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, wisdom is cleansed by ethics, and ethics are cleansed by "
"wisdom."

msgctxt "dn4:22.7"
msgid "Yattha sīlaṃ tattha paññā, yattha paññā tattha sīlaṃ."
msgstr "Ethics and wisdom always go together."

msgctxt "dn4:22.8"
msgid "Sīlavato paññā, paññavato sīlaṃ."
msgstr "An ethical person is wise, and a wise person ethical."

msgctxt "dn4:22.9"
msgid "Sīlapaññāṇañca pana lokasmiṃ aggamakkhāyati."
msgstr "And ethics and wisdom are said to be the best things in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc62"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:22.10"
msgid "Katamaṃ pana taṃ, brāhmaṇa, sīlaṃ?"
msgstr "But what, brahmin, is that ethical conduct?"

msgctxt "dn4:22.11"
msgid "Katamā sā paññā”ti?"
msgstr "And what is that wisdom?”"

msgctxt "dn4:22.12"
msgid "“Ettakaparamāva mayaṃ, bho gotama, etasmiṃ atthe."
msgstr "“That’s all I know about this matter, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "dn4:22.13"
msgid "Sādhu vata bhavantaṃyeva gotamaṃ paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho”ti."
msgstr "May Master Gotama himself please clarify the meaning of this.”"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs23"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:23.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇohi, sādhukaṃ manasikarohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn4:23.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes sir,” Soṇadaṇḍa replied."

msgctxt "dn4:23.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

msgctxt "dn4:23.4"
msgid "“idha, brāhmaṇa, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened "
"Buddha …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics."

msgctxt "dn4:23.6"
msgid "Idaṃ kho taṃ, brāhmaṇa, sīlaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "This, brahmin, is that ethical conduct. …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.7"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati …"
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.8"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.9"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.10"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …"
msgstr "fourth absorption …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.11"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati, abhininnāmeti … pe …"
msgstr "They extend and project the mind toward knowledge and vision …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.12"
msgid "Idampissa hoti paññāya … pe …"
msgstr "This pertains to their wisdom. …"

msgctxt "dn4:23.13"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn4:23.14"
msgid "Idampissa hoti paññāya "
msgstr "This pertains to their wisdom. "

msgctxt "dn4:23.15"
msgid "ayaṃ kho sā, brāhmaṇa, paññā”ti."
msgstr "This, brahmin, is that wisdom.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn4:23.16"
msgid "7. Soṇadaṇḍaupāsakattapaṭivedanā"
msgstr "7. Soṇadaṇḍa Declares Himself a Lay Follower"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs24"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.125"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc63"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:24.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Soṇadaṇḍa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn4:24.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn4:24.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the Teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "dn4:24.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn4:24.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life."

msgctxt "dn4:24.6"
msgid ""
"Adhivāsetu ca me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Would you and the Order of monks please accept a meal from me tomorrow?”"

msgctxt "dn4:24.7"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc64"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:24.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, Soṇadaṇḍa got up from his seat, "
"bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

msgctxt "dn4:24.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ "
"khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi:"
msgstr ""
"And when the night had passed Soṇadaṇḍa had a variety of delicious foods "
"prepared in his own home. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn4:24.10"
msgid "“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.”"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs25"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:25.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṅghena yena soṇadaṇḍassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of Soṇadaṇḍa together with the mendicant Saṅgha, where he sat on "
"the seat spread out."

msgctxt "dn4:25.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena "
"khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi."
msgstr ""
"Then Soṇadaṇḍa served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the "
"Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs26"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.126"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc65"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:26.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ "
"nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Soṇadaṇḍa took a low "
"seat and sat to one side."

msgctxt "dn4:26.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho soṇadaṇḍo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side he said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn4:26.3"
msgid ""
"“ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, parisagato samāno āsanā vuṭṭhahitvā "
"bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ abhivādeyyaṃ, tena maṃ sā parisā paribhaveyya."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, if, when I have gone to an assembly, I rise from my seat and "
"bow to the Buddha, that assembly might disparage me for that."

msgctxt "dn4:26.4"
msgid "Yaṃ kho pana sā parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha."
msgstr "And when you’re disparaged by the assembly, your reputation diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:26.5"
msgid "Yassa kho pana yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr "When your reputation diminishes, your wealth also diminishes."

msgctxt "dn4:26.6"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr "But my wealth relies on my reputation."

msgctxt "dn4:26.7"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, parisagato samāno añjaliṃ paggaṇheyyaṃ, āsanā "
"me taṃ bhavaṃ gotamo paccuṭṭhānaṃ dhāretu."
msgstr ""
"If, when I have gone to an assembly, I raise my joined palms, please take it "
"that I have risen from my seat."

msgctxt "dn4:26.8"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, parisagato samāno veṭhanaṃ omuñceyyaṃ, sirasā "
"me taṃ bhavaṃ gotamo abhivādanaṃ dhāretu."
msgstr "And if I undo my turban, please take it that I have bowed."

msgctxt "dn4:26.9"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, yānagato samāno yānā paccorohitvā bhavantaṃ "
"gotamaṃ abhivādeyyaṃ, tena maṃ sā parisā paribhaveyya."
msgstr ""
"And Master Gotama, if, when I am in a carriage, I rise from my seat and bow "
"to the Buddha, that assembly might disparage me for that."

msgctxt "dn4:26.10"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho pana sā parisā paribhaveyya, yasopi tassa hāyetha, yassa kho pana "
"yaso hāyetha, bhogāpi tassa hāyeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:26.11"
msgid "Yasoladdhā kho panamhākaṃ bhogā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn4:26.12"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, yānagato samāno patodalaṭṭhiṃ abbhunnāmeyyaṃ, "
"yānā me taṃ bhavaṃ gotamo paccorohanaṃ dhāretu."
msgstr ""
"If, when I am in a carriage, I hold up my goad, please take it that I have "
"got down from my carriage."

msgctxt "dn4:26.13"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana, bho gotama, yānagato samāno chattaṃ apanāmeyyaṃ, sirasā "
"me taṃ bhavaṃ gotamo abhivādanaṃ dhāretū”ti."
msgstr "And if I lower my sunshade, please take it that I have bowed.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc66"></a>
msgctxt "dn4:27.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā soṇadaṇḍaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā "
"samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired the brahmin "
"Soṇadaṇḍa with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn4:27.2"
msgid "Soṇadaṇḍasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
